# widget — data layer boundary

The widget talks to the backend through ONE narrow seam. Keep it that way as
the real UI lands in W3/W4.

## Invariants

- **All API access goes through `src/api/chatClient.ts`.** No raw `fetch`,
  `axios`, or `XMLHttpRequest` in components, hooks, or anywhere else.
- **Components read and write chat state via the Zustand store**
  (`src/store/chatStore.ts`) — never call `chatClient` directly from a
  component. Components dispatch actions (`sendMessage`, `submitFeedback`,
  `reset`) and read with selectors (`useChatStore((s) => s.messages)`). Feedback
  thumbs (L4) MUST go through `submitFeedback`, not a raw `sendFeedback` call.
- **The backend contract types live in `chatClient.ts`** and MUST match the API
  routes exactly — update both together:
  - `/chat` (`ChatMessage`, `ChatSource`, `ChatResponse`) ↔
    `packages/api/src/routes/chat.ts`. `ChatResponse` includes
    `logId: number | null` (best-effort observability id) and the debug pair
    `retrieval: RetrievalDebugItem[]` + `minScoreUsed: number` (D1/D2):
    `retrieval` is the full top-K set with per-item `passedThreshold` flags and
    is ALWAYS populated, incl. on refusal — distinct from `sources` (chunks the
    answer used, `[]` on refusal); don't conflate them. The store holds these as
    `lastRetrieval` / `lastMinScore` and `RetrievalDebugPanel` (a dev-only test
    harness surface) reads them. Note the response has no `threadTitle` /
    `subject` / `dateRange` fields — those were removed.
  - `/feedback` (`sendFeedback(logId, rating)`) ↔
    `packages/api/src/routes/feedback.ts`. Body is
    `{ logId, rating: "up" | "down" | null }` (`null` clears the rating — undo);
    success is `{ status: "ok" }`, unknown `logId` is `404`. The store retains
    the latest answer's `logId` (`lastLogId`) and attaches feedback to it.
- **Feedback toggle logic lives in the store, not the route/repo.**
  `submitFeedback("up" | "down")` derives the next value (re-clicking the active
  rating → `null` undo; clicking the other → switch) and sends it. The route and
  `setFeedback` are dumb writers that persist whatever value they're given
  (including `null`). Callers (L4 buttons) just call `submitFeedback("up")` /
  `submitFeedback("down")`.
- **The backend is single-turn:** `sendChat` sends only the last user message,
  not history. Don't quietly switch to multi-turn here without also changing
  the API.
- **Base URL comes from `src/config.ts` (`apiUrl`)** — don't read
  `import.meta.env` or hardcode URLs elsewhere.

## Why

This seam keeps networking testable and the store the single source of truth
for chat state, so UI work (W3) and the typewriter effect (W4) can't smuggle in
ad-hoc network calls or contract drift.
